#File S7: MergeMap consensus genetic map for Pinus taeda and Pinus elliottii with genomic sequence alignments and predicted genes functions based on transcript alignments,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
"#Legend: MergeMarkerID - identifier of marker used in input maps to allow consensus map merging, GeneSeqID - identifier used in alignment analysis of a marker's sequence (see File S5), LG - linkage group, LG_pos_cM - centiMorgan position of the locus in the linkage group, Pos_lCI - cM position of the lower bound of locus 95% confidence interval, Pos_uCI - cM position of the upper bound of locus 95% CI, Delta_CIbounds - cM difference between upper and lower 95% CI, MarkerID - identifier for the specific marker allele mapped in a contributing input map, Marker_type - type of allele segregating for the locus (SNP - single nucleotide polymorphism; RFLP - restriction fragment length polymorphism; PAV - presence-absence variant; SSR - simple sequence repeat; estSSR - SSR from an expressed sequence tag; ESTP - expressed sequence tag polymorphism), Seg_qtl-base1 - the present or absent in the qtl-base1 map, Seg_qtl-base2 - present or absent in the qtl-base2 map, Seg_BC1 - present or absent in the BC1 map, Seg_10-5 - present (1) or absent (0) in the 10-5 map, Aligned_scaff_ID - scaffold or contig identifier of Pinus taeda RefSeq assembly v1.01, Aligned_genome_coord - start position..stop position for the best alignment  of the scaffold_ID with the marker GeneSeqID, Genome_pct_aligned - percent nucleotide sequence aligned length between the marker and P. taeda genome sequence, Genome_pct_ID - percent nucleotide sequence identity between the marker and aligned P. taeda genome sequence, Aligned_transcript(Accession_Pending) - predicted full-length Pinus taeda trascript ID - not yet assigned pending publication by Mockaitis et al., ESTvTr_pctID - percent nucleotide sequence identity between the EST marker and transcript, ESTvTr_alignlen - nucleotide length of alignment between the EST marker and transcript, ESTvTr_evalue - E-value of alignment between the EST marker and transcript, ESTvTr_bitscore - Bitscore of alignment between the EST marker and transcript, Aligned_CDD -  NCBI Conserved Domain Database accessionID assigned to the transcript, CDD_desc - description of the protein domain from the NCBI Conserved domain database, Tr_CDD_pctID - percent sequence identity between the transcript and the domain from the NCBI CDD, Tr_CDD_alignlen - length of alignment between the transcript and the domain  , Tr_CDD_evalue - E-value of alignment between the transcript and the domain, Tr_CDD_bitscore - Bitscore of alignment between the transcript and the domain, Aligned_AGI_prot - TAIR accession ID of the Arabidosis AGI map gene model with the highest amino acid sequence identity with the assigned translated P. taeda transcript, Prot_desc - description of the protein function of the TAIR gene model, Tr_AGI_pctID - percent amino acid sequence identity between the Arabidopsis and P. taeda proteins, Tr_AGI_alignlen - length of alignment between Arabidopsis and P. taeda transcripts, Tr_AGI_evalue - E-value of alignment between Arabidopsis and P.taeda transcripts, Tr_AGI_bitscore - Bitscore of alignment between Arabidopsis and P.taeda transcripts, MarkerAcc - NCBI/GenBank accession number for the marker sequence or for the best blastn match to the marker sequence, NP - the gene is reported on the 10-5 map3 of Neves et al. 2014 but was not positioned on our consensus map, NA - information not available."
